repos/pytorch/pytorch/pulls/6283", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "_links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.github.com/repos/pytorch/pytorch/pulls/comments/179575103"}, "html": {"href": "https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/pull/6283#discussion_r179575103"}, "pull_request": {"href": "https://api.github.com/repos/pytorch/pytorch/pulls/6283"}}, "body_html": "<p>Yes.  To put it more explicitly, this controls whether <code>DeviceSpec.device_index</code> returns None or not.  So there is a distinction between <code>cuda</code> and <code>cuda:0</code> (because the default cuda device can change).</p>", "body_text": "Yes.  To put it more explicitly, this controls whether DeviceSpec.device_index returns None or not.  So there is a distinction between cuda and cuda:0 (because the default cuda device can change).", "in_reply_to_id": 179568690}